<figureCitation id="6AC3EE9D16615C96FA5F09B083834EF1" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Distribution map of L. demissus (black circles), L. paniculatus (open circles), and L. velozianus (black stars) on Hispaniola." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.172.59497.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/502599" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4</figureCitation>
). Given the extent of tropical dry forest in and around that area, it is very likely that more localities of this species will be found.
</paragraph>
